    <note>Hu(1) Yuqian [18888] After his father died, shortly after Yuqian's birth, his mother remarried into the Yu(6) family. When Yuqian earned the jinshi, he assumed his natural father's surname, Hu, but changed his mingzi to Yu(6)qian in order to demonstrate that he had not forgotten the benevolence of the Yu(6) in raising him. Liu Kezhuang, WJ, 154.10a-13b; Zhejiang TZ, 127.4b. CBD, 2, 1595-6.</note>
